<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 828.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-02"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 2, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I transmit herewith, for your further
                            information on the subject, a copy of a memorandum of this date, and of
                            the paper therein referred to, relative to the examination of Drs. Almon
                            and Smith and Mr. A. Keith, jr., charged with having obstructed the
                            execution of a warrant for the arrest of Wade and others, of the pirates
                            engaged in the Chesapeake affair.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles F. Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                            <p>[The enclosures referred to will be found among correspondence with
                                the British legation, in this volume.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>